com.revolverobotics.kubiapi
Interface IKubiManagerDelegate

public interface IKubiManagerDelegate

This interface provides notifications about the status of KubiManager as well as the status of the connection to a kubi and the result of a kubi search.

Author:
Oliver Rice

Method Detail

kubiDeviceFound

void kubiDeviceFound(KubiManager manager,
                     KubiSearchResult device)
Called when KubiManager.findKubi() successfully finds a kubi. This method allows the delegate to decide whether to connect to the found kubi or not. To connect simply call manager.connectToKubi(device).

Parameters:
manager - The KubiManager that found the device.
device - The result of the kubi search

kubiManagerStatusChanged

void kubiManagerStatusChanged(KubiManager manager,
                              int oldStatus,
                              int newStatus)
Called when the status of the KubiManager changes.

Parameters:
manager - The KubiManager that changed its status
oldStatus - The status that the KubiManager had previous to the change.
newStatus - The new status of the KubiManager

kubiManagerFailed

void kubiManagerFailed(KubiManager manager,
                       int reason)
Called when a problem occurred, causing the previous action to fail.

Parameters:
manager - The KubiManager that experienced the problem.
reason - The reason for the failure

kubiScanComplete

void kubiScanComplete(KubiManager manager,
                      java.util.ArrayList<KubiSearchResult> device)
Called when the findAllKubis() command has completed successfully. This will be called at least 2 seconds after calling findAllKubis().

Parameters:
manager - The KubiManager that completed the scan.
device - The list of devices found
